io.spine.server.event

Class AbstractEventSubscriber

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.spine.server.event.AbstractEventSubscriber
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    io.spine.logging.Logging, MessageDispatcher<io.spine.core.EventClass,io.spine.core.EventEnvelope,java.util.Set<java.lang.String>>, MulticastDispatcher<io.spine.core.EventClass,io.spine.core.EventEnvelope,java.lang.String>, EventDispatcher<java.lang.String>, EventReceiver, EventSubscriber, ExternalDispatcherFactory<java.lang.String>

    public abstract class AbstractEventSubscriber
extends java.lang.Object
implements EventDispatcher<java.lang.String>, EventSubscriber, io.spine.logging.Logging
    The abstract base for objects that can be subscribed to receive events from EventBus.

    Objects may also receive events via EventDispatchers that can be registered with EventBus.

    See Also:
    Bus.register(MessageDispatcher), {@code @Subscribe} annotation for declaring event subscriptions in the derived classes

      • canDispatch

        public boolean canDispatch(io.spine.core.EventEnvelope envelope)
        Description copied from interface: MessageDispatcher
        Checks if this dispatcher can dispatch the given message.

        This method does not check that the type of the message is one of the dispatched message classes. Instead, it validates the message upon some custom rules of this dispatcher.

        Extend this method to forbid messages from being dispatched to this instance.

        Specified by:
        canDispatch in interface MessageDispatcher<io.spine.core.EventClass,io.spine.core.EventEnvelope,java.util.Set<java.lang.String>>
        Parameters:
        envelope - the message to check
        Returns:
        true is the given message can be dispatched by this dispatcher, false otherwise
